	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I think the question should be defined differently, 'is there a reason for backtracking'. If it is not adds anything (or much) to gameplay, it is not needed.
<br />
<br />In a game with one-axis scrolling a reason for backtracking could be inertia, when you need to take a run to perform long jump. It was a (minor) problem in SMB, and major problem in Kid Kool.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
