		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">Shiru wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">I think the question should be defined differently, 'is there a reason for backtracking'. If it is not adds anything (or much) to gameplay, it is not needed.</div>
<br />Also having no backtracking is a gameplay element by itself. For example, in the beginning of 1-1 in SMB1 there's a spot where you can either go down a pipe or get a hidden 1-UP <em>or</em> do both if you're careful (to not have the screen scroll past the pipe). In that sense, the limitation contributes to the gameplay.

		

